  "fun_facts": [
    "Related to Milk of Magnesia - the liquid antacid is a suspension of magnesium hydroxide (which forms from magnesium oxide + water)",
    "Used as an antacid and laxative for over a century - still sold as 'Phillips' Milk of Magnesia'",
    "Has an extremely high melting point (2,852°C) - used in refractory materials for furnaces",
    "Provides both anti-caking properties AND magnesium supplementation in foods",
    "Tasteless and odorless, making it ideal for use in delicate foods",
    "Can absorb moisture from air, slowly converting to magnesium hydroxide and then magnesium carbonate"
